Plugins, and Related Extensions.

  This Software supports loading third-party tools and third-party
plugins through a modular system. We encourage community developers to
build third-party tools and third-party plugins for this Software, but
they must follow these requirements:

  a) Independent License: Third-party tools and third-party plugins
  loaded as independent dynamic link libraries (DLLs) or in other
  forms may have independent licenses, provided that the codebase of
  such third-party tool or third-party plugin does not contain
  protected core code, undisclosed implementations, private
  interfaces, security mechanisms, or other content protected under
  this Agreement from the Software, built-in tools, or built-in
  plugins;

  b) Compliant Interaction: Third-party tools and third-party plugins
  interacting with the main program of the Software may not include
  functions intended to circumvent the restrictions in Section 2 of
  this Agreement. It is strictly prohibited to develop or distribute
  any third-party tools or third-party plugins that can be used to
  hide advertisements of the main program, built-in tools, or
  built-in plugins, crack main program limitations, bypass login,
  forge or intercept APIs, interfere with updates, undermine access
  control, affect security mechanisms, or obstruct the normal display
  and operation of official content;

  c) Official Inclusion: If you wish to merge your third-party tool or
  third-party plugin into Team APE:RIP's official code repository,
  official release versions, built-in tool system, or built-in plugin
  system, you must agree to license it to Team APE:RIP under this
